# Festag auth — fields + white CTAs

## Inputs (`.al-input`)

- **Never** use a visible focus ring on hover/focus/typing/autofill
- Feedback is **fill only** (`--festag-input-fill` → `--festag-input-fill-focus`)
- Override global `*:focus-visible` with `outline: none !important` on `.al-root .al-input`

## White CTAs (Weiter, SSO, Apple, Docs „Alle anzeigen“)

Canonical look = **AuthDocs `auth-docs-all`**:

- Fill: `#ffffff`
- **Light hairline stroke**: `1px solid rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12)`
- Soft bottom 3D lift (not a hard platform bar alone):
  - `0 1px 0 rgba(15,23,42,.05), 0 1px 3px rgba(15,23,42,.08)`
- Hover: slightly stronger border + shadow
- Active: inset press

**Critical:** Define `--festag-btn-dark-*` on `.al-root` itself. Do not rely on `html` theme tokens — dark html tokens make white-page CTAs translucent and look invisible.

Keep `.al-btn-primary`, `.al-btn-ghost`, `.al-btn-apple`, and `.auth-docs-all` on the same tokens.

Google stays branded slate.

## Do not

- Borderless white-on-white CTAs (invisible)
- Heavy multi-layer marketing shadows
- Letting portal dark tokens leak into auth light buttons
